<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910711-0060</DOCNO><DOCID>910711-0060.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Spar Aerospace Ltd.:   Contract for $200.4 Million   To Build Satellite Is Won</HL><DATE>07/11/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   T.SPZ</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><GV>COMMERCE DEPARTMENT (COM)FEDERAL GOVERNMENT (FDL)</GV><RE>ALASKA (AK)CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Spar Aerospace Ltd. said it received a 230 millionCanadian dollar (US$200.4 million) contract from the CanadianSpace Agency to construct the Radarsat satellite.   Construction of the spacecraft is due to be completed byAugust 1993, when testing will begin. The launch date isscheduled for early 1995. Spar received a C$146 millioncontract last year to design the satellite.</LP><TEXT>   The data recorded by the satellite over its five-year lifewill be used primarily in the management of naturalresources, control of ship movements, ice information,oil-slick monitoring, mapping, geological information andother environmental uses.   The Radarsat program is a Canadian-led internationalproject. The U.S. National Aeronautics and SpaceAdministration will provide the launch of the satellite andwill operate a data reception station in Alaska in exchangefor radar data needed for its research programs and those ofthe U.S. Department of Commerce's National Oceanic andAtmospheric Administration.</TEXT></DOC>